DOC.brief_summary: A study designed to look at how the drug AZD8566 is taken up by the body when given with or without food. In some subjects a comparison will be made with a very small labelled microdose given into a vein.
DOC.criteria: Provision of written informed consent Clinically normal physical findings and laboratory values as judged by the investigator with normal ECG Females who are permanently or surgically sterile or postmenopausal and males History of any convulsions or seizures History of infection or risk of infection due to recent surgery or trauma History or presence of conditions know to interfere with the absorption, distribution, metabolism and excretion of the study drug
